snippet.textDisplay:
To be fair, when pilots dump fuel, they have ask the air control if/when/where they can dump fuel.
So whoever was in the tower gave them the clear to dump all that fuel over those schools.

EDIT: I'm not saying fuel dumping didn't save lives, I'm saying there's always a safer place to do it to minimise injuries on ground. ATC know when and where ìts safe to do these things.
As someone points out below, Apparently the pilot initially said they didn't need to dump fuel, but then did so later WITHOUT notifying tower/ATC so therefore ATC are not at fault.

There are emergency landings/fuel dumps all the time, and there is a reason you don't here about them on the news 24/7.
